description:
Initial position: Start with weights in each hand, straight back and feet separated to the width of the hips.Your arms must be relaxed, pointing down.Your knees must be slightly flexed, your abs contracted and your shoulders down. & Nbsp; steps: & nbsp;
1. Fold an arm by the elbow, carrying the dumbbell to your shoulder.The upper arm must remain motionless during this movement.2. Take the dumbbell down until your arm is in its original relaxed position. & NBSP;
3. Repeat, changing arm.

Stand upright with your chest slightly raised, your feet hip-width apart and your toes pointing straight ahead.

Bring your hands to the back of your head with your fingers slightly interlaced and your elbows pointing to the side. Push your hips back and bend your knees, keeping your upper body as upright as possible.&nbsp;

Push your knees outwards, they must never point towards each other. If your upper body moves slightly forward, make sure that it does not bend. Always keep your elbows level with your ears by tensing the muscles between your shoulder blades. If you are flexible enough, you can sink down until your buttocks touch your calves.
However, make sure that you do not bend your spine.&nbsp;

Before this happens, reverse the movement and use your heels and glutes to push yourself upwards with so much momentum that your feet lift off briefly and you do a little hop.&nbsp;

If necessary, correct the position of your feet, arms and upper body before you move on to the next repetition.

Translated with www.DeepL.com/Translator (free version)

Go to the push -up position, your shoulders are located directly above your hands, your feet are hip width apart. & Nbsp;
Make sure that your body forms a straight line from the head to the heels. & Nbsp;

Now pull your right knee towards the chest.While the knee stays bent, you lift your right leg as far as possible, the right lower leg is pointing up. & Nbsp;

Now turn your hip so that your right foot swings over your left leg.Rotate and move your right foot towards the floor until you are forced to roll on the outside of your left foot.Make sure that you do not take your upper body. & Nbsp;

Now return to the starting position and repeat the exercise with the right leg.
